@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix ids: <https://w3id.org/idsa/core/> .
@prefix idsc: <https://w3id.org/idsa/code/> .
@prefix idsm: <https://w3id.org/idsa/metamodel/> .
@prefix sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix shapes: <https://github.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/> .


shapes:ConnectorbasedOfferTemplateShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass ids:ConnectorbasedOffer ;
    sh:property shapes:ConnectorbasedOfferTemplate-permissionPropertyShape ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/ConnectorbasedAgreementTemplates/ConnectorbasedOfferTemplateShape.ttl> (ConnectorbasedOfferTemplateShape): In a _:ConnectorbasedOffer a) the ids:provider property must point to one participant or b) the ids:consumer property must point to one participant  or c) the ids:provider and the ids:consumer must point to one participant. This can in any case be a) an IRI or b) an ids:Participant. The ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission the ids:assigner, ids:assignee, ids:target and ids:action properties have to be specified. The ids:constraint property must point to an ids:Constraint with ids:leftOperand idsc:SYSTEM, ids:operator idsc:SAME_AS and ids:rightOperandReference pointing to the ConnectorUri."@en ;
.


shapes:ConnectorbasedOfferTemplate-permissionPropertyShape
    a sh:PropertyShape ;
    sh:path ids:permission ;
    sh:node shapes:ConnectorbasedOfferPermissionTemplate ;
    sh:minCount 1 ;
    sh:maxCount 1 ;
    sh:severity sh:Violation ;
    sh:message "<https://raw.githubusercontent.com/International-Data-Spaces-Association/InformationModel/master/examples/contract-and-usage-policy/templates/ConnectorbasedAgreementTemplates/ConnectorbasedOfferTemplateShape.ttl> (ConnectorbasedOfferTemplate-permissionPropertyShape): In a _:ConnectorbasedOffer the ids:permission property must point to at exactly one ids:Permission. In the ids:Permission, the ids:target and ids:action properties and one of (ids:assigner and ids:assignee) have to be specified. The ids:constraint property must point to an ids:Constraint with ids:leftOperand idsc:SYSTEM, ids:operator idsc:SAME_AS and ids:rightOperandReference pointing to the ConnectorUri."@en ;
.


shapes:ConnectorbasedOfferPermissionTemplate
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:HasAssignerOrAssigneeNodeShape ;
    sh:property shapes:PermissionTemplate-targetPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:PermissionTemplate-actionPropertyShape ;
    sh:property shapes:ConnectorbasedPermissionTemplate-constraintPropertyShape ;
.
